The paper deals with graph partitioning problems, which are typically studied in the areas of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and theoretical computer science (cs.IT). The use of expansion properties of graphs is also a common theme in spectral graph theory (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper presents approximation algorithms, which are often studied in computational geometry (cs.CG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
